| **License** | MIT |

---

## How It Works

The agent uses **two separate concepts** in `.env`:

| Role | Variables | Purpose |
|------|-----------|---------|
| **Login account** | `YOUTUBE_EMAIL`, `YOUTUBE_PASSWORD` | The Google account used to sign in, browse YouTube, and post replies |
| **Target channel** | `YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_NAME`, `YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_URL` | The **specific channel** where work is performed — this does **not** have to be the login account's channel |

### Runtime flow

```
1. Log in          →  YOUTUBE_EMAIL / YOUTUBE_PASSWORD
2. Open channel    →  YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_NAME (or YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_URL)
3. Latest video    →  Agent opens the target channel's most recent upload
4. Analyze         →  Scrape comments, classify sentiment, detect unanswered
5. Reply           →  Generate (and optionally post) AI replies on that video
6. Report          →  Generate PDF and optionally email it
```

```
┌──────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────────────┐      ┌────────────────────────┐
│  Login Account   │      │   Target Channel          │      │   Latest Video         │
│  (your .env      │ ───▶ │   YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_NAME    │ ───▶ │   Comments scraped,    │
│   credentials)   │      │   e.g. MrBeast            │      │   analyzed & replied   │
└──────────────────┘      └─────────────────────────┘      └────────────────────────┘
```

> **Example:** You log in as `manager@gmail.com`, set `YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_NAME=MrBeast`, click **Analyze** — the agent signs in, goes to the MrBeast channel, opens its latest video, and runs the full pipeline on that video's comments.

---

## Features

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Browser automation** | Playwright-based YouTube login with session persistence |
| **YouTube login** | Automated Google sign-in via login credentials in `.env` |
| **Target channel navigation** | Opens the specific channel set in `YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_NAME` |
| **Latest video analysis** | Scrapes and analyzes comments on the channel's most recent video |
| **Sentiment analysis** | LLM classification: positive, negative, neutral, question, suggestion, spam |
| **AI-generated replies** | Community-manager-style responses filtered by category |
| **Automated posting** | Optional browser-based reply posting on the target video |
| **HTML dashboard report** | Comprehensive video + comment dashboard with LLM executive summary |
| **PDF reporting** | ReportLab summary reports with tables |
| **Email automation** | Gmail SMTP delivery with PDF attachments |
| **LangGraph workflows** | Linear pipeline with 13 graph nodes |
| **Streamlit UI** | Dashboard with channel inputs and metric widgets |

---

## Workflow

```
START
  → prepare_input
  → decision_agent
  → login_youtube              ← sign in with YOUTUBE_EMAIL
  → fetch_channel_data         ← open YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_NAME → latest video
  → analyze_comments
  → generate_replies
  → post_replies
  → generate_html_report    ← comprehensive dashboard (.html)
  → generate_pdf_report
  → email_report            ← emails HTML + PDF when EMAIL_REPORTS=true
  → END
```

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Orchestration | LangGraph `StateGraph` |
| LLM | Groq `llama-3.1-8b-instant` |
| Browser | Playwright (Chromium) |
| PDF | ReportLab |
| Email | Gmail SMTP |
| UI | Streamlit |

---

## Quick Start

### 1. Install dependencies

```bash
./setup.sh
```

Or manually:

```bash
uv sync
uv run playwright install chromium
cp .env.example .env
```

### 2. Configure `.env`

```env
# LLM
GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_your_key_here

# Login account (used to sign in and post replies)
YOUTUBE_EMAIL=manager@gmail.com
YOUTUBE_PASSWORD=your_password_here

# Target channel (where the agent does its work — any channel)
YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_NAME=MrBeast
YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_URL=

# Safety defaults
ENABLE_COMMENT_REPLIES=false
EMAIL_REPORTS=false
```

| Variable | What it does |
|----------|--------------|
| `YOUTUBE_EMAIL` / `YOUTUBE_PASSWORD` | Signs into YouTube |
| `YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_NAME` | Navigates to this channel and works on its **latest video** |
| `YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_URL` | Optional — use instead of name if you have the direct URL |

### 3. Run the UI

```bash
./start.sh ui
```

Open `http://localhost:8501` and click **Analyze**. The UI pre-fills the channel name from `YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_NAME` — you can override it per run.

---

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `GROQ_API_KEY` | — | Required for LLM analysis and replies |
| `YOUTUBE_EMAIL` | — | **Login account** — signs into YouTube |
| `YOUTUBE_PASSWORD` | — | **Login account** password |
| `YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_NAME` | — | **Target channel** name (e.g. `MrBeast`) — latest video is analyzed |
| `YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_URL` | — | Optional target channel URL (skips name search) |
| `ENABLE_COMMENT_REPLIES` | `false` | Post replies on the target video |
| `EMAIL_REPORTS` | `false` | Email HTML dashboard + PDF reports |
| `REPLY_TO_POSITIVE` | `true` | Generate replies for positive comments |
| `REPLY_TO_NEGATIVE` | `false` | Generate replies for negative comments |
| `REPLY_TO_NEUTRAL` | `false` | Generate replies for neutral comments |
| `REPLY_TO_QUESTIONS` | `true` | Generate replies for questions |
| `REPLY_TO_SUGGESTIONS` | `true` | Generate replies for suggestions |
| `REPLY_TO_SPAM` | `false` | Generate replies for spam |
| `BROWSER_HEADLESS` | `true` | Run browser without visible window |
| `MAX_VIDEOS_TO_SCAN` | `1` | Videos to scan (`1` = latest video only) |
| `MAX_COMMENTS_PER_VIDEO` | `20` | Max comments scraped per video |
| `GMAIL_SMTP_USER` | — | Sender email for reports |
| `GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD` | — | Gmail app password |
| `GMAIL_DEFAULT_RECIPIENT` | — | Default report recipient |

---

## Project Structure

```
src/agent/
├── graph.py                  # LangGraph definition (13 nodes)
├── config.py                 # Login + target channel config from .env
├── routing.py                # YouTube intent detection
├── task_planner.py           # Workflow task planning
├── workflow_executor.py      # Pipeline step execution
└── custom_tools/
    ├── browser_tools.py      # Playwright login & session
    ├── youtube_tools.py      # Target channel navigation & comment scraping
    ├── comment_analyzer.py   # LLM comment classification
    ├── reply_generator.py    # AI reply generation
    ├── pdf_generator.py      # PDF report generation
    ├── html_report_generator.py  # HTML dashboard reports
    └── email_tools.py        # Gmail SMTP
streamlit_ui.py               # Dashboard UI
```

---

## Reply Filter Examples

Configure any combination in `.env`:

- **Positive only:** `REPLY_TO_POSITIVE=true`, all others `false`
- **Questions + Suggestions:** `REPLY_TO_QUESTIONS=true`, `REPLY_TO_SUGGESTIONS=true`
- **All categories:** Set all `REPLY_TO_*` to `true`

When `ENABLE_COMMENT_REPLIES=false`, replies are generated but **not posted** to the target video.

---

## Commands

```bash
./start.sh ui       # Streamlit dashboard → :8501
./start.sh server   # LangGraph Studio → :2024
./start.sh both     # Both services
./start.sh stop     # Stop services
```

